						               													<description>Bomb Run is designed to provide the framework of an immersive and sometimes emotional experience that may or may not have a happy ending. No mission will be the same but it is your story and your imagination forms the narrative.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each game simulates a World War II Bombing mission over Europe in a B17G Flying Fortress. Each mission builds on the last mission with the ultimate objective to get as much of the 10-man crew through the required 25 missions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will physically mark on the crew cards to show their record of downed enemy planes and completed missions. Use a sharpee. The cards are coated with a UV protection which allows you to clean your card off with an alcohol swab to reset it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bomb Run is a solitaire, deck-in-hand, card game. That means there is no table-top required and the entire game fits in the player&amp;rsquo;s hand. Each mission takes on average less than 10 minutes but it can easily be put away and picked up later and continued mid-mission.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
